#Function to plot Pie-Charts for all categorical variables in the dataframe
def pie_charts_for_CategoricalVar(t_merg,m):
   # '''Takes in a dataframe(t_merg) and plots pie charts for all categorical columns. m = number of columns required in grid'''
    
    #get all the column names in the dataframe
    a = []
    for i in t_merg:
        a.append(i)
    
    #isolate the categorical variable names from a to b
    b = []
    for i in a:
        if (t_merg[i].dtype.name) == 'object':
            b.append(i)
        
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 12))
    plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.2)
    plt.suptitle("Pie-Charts for Categorical Variables in the dataframe", fontsize=18, y=0.95)
    
    # number of columns, as inputted while calling the function
    ncols = m
    # calculate number of rows
    nrows = len(b) // ncols + (len(b) % ncols > 0)
    
    # loop through the length of 'b' and keep track of index
    for n, i in enumerate(b):
        # add a new subplot iteratively using nrows and ncols
        ax = plt.subplot(nrows, ncols, n + 1)

        # filter df and plot 'i' on the new subplot axis
        t_merg.groupby(i).size().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%.2f%%',ax=ax)
        
        ax.set_title(i.upper())
        ax.set_xlabel("")
        ax.set_ylabel("")
    plt.show()

import scipy.stats as stats

for i in t_merg:
  crosstab=pd.crosstab(t_merg['Churn'],t_merg[i])
  chi_sq_Stat, p_value, deg_freedom, exp_freq = stats.chi2_contingency(crosstab)

  print('Chi-square statistic: %3.5f , P value:  %1.6f' %(chi_sq_Stat, p_value))

  if p_value < 0.05:  # Setting our significance level at 5%
        print('Rejecting Null Hypothesis: Customer who Churn and who do not Churn does NOT have same distribution of {}'.format(i))
        print('\n')
  else:
        print('Fail to Reject Null Hypothesis: Customer who Churn and who do not Churn have same distribution of {}'.format(i))
        print('\n')

from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, accuracy_score, classification_report
import time

def evaluate(model, X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test, duration):
    y_test_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    y_train_pred = model.predict(X_train)

    print('{}'.format('\033[1m'))
    print("TRAINIG RESULTS: \n===============================")
    clf_report = pd.DataFrame(classification_report(y_train, y_train_pred, output_dict=True))
    print(f"CONFUSION MATRIX:\n{confusion_matrix(y_train, y_train_pred)}")
    print(f"ACCURACY SCORE:\n{accuracy_score(y_train, y_train_pred):.4f}")
    print(f"CLASSIFICATION REPORT:\n{clf_report}")
    print("\n")

    print("TESTING RESULTS: \n===============================")
    clf_report = pd.DataFrame(classification_report(y_test, y_test_pred, output_dict=True))
    print(f"CONFUSION MATRIX:\n{confusion_matrix(y_test, y_test_pred)}")
    print(f"ACCURACY SCORE:\n{accuracy_score(y_test, y_test_pred):.4f}")
    print(f"CLASSIFICATION REPORT:\n{clf_report}")
    print("\n")
    print("TIME ELAPSED : ", duration)

def timer(start_time=None):
    if not start_time:
        start_time = datetime.now()
        return start_time
    elif start_time:
        thour, temp_sec = divmod((datetime.now() - start_time).total_seconds(), 3600)
        tmin, tsec = divmod(temp_sec, 60)
        print('\n Time taken: %i hours %i minutes and %s seconds.' % (thour, tmin, round(tsec, 2)))

def seg_iv_dv(tel_df, tf_v):
    #Segregate Dependent and Independet Features
    iv=tel_df.drop(tf_v,axis=1)
    tf=pd.DataFrame(tel_df[[tf_v]])
    return iv,tf

def seg_cat_num(iv):
    #Segregate Catagorical and Numerical Features
    catv=iv.drop(['SeniorCitizen','tenure','MonthlyCharges'],axis=1)
    numv=pd.DataFrame(iv[['SeniorCitizen','tenure','MonthlyCharges']])
    return catv,numv

def merge_df(a,b):
    #Merge DataFrame
    c= pd.merge(a,b,left_index=True, right_index=True)
    return c

#Imputing missing values
def imputmissing(numv, tel_df):
    #Impute missing Values
    percent_missing= numv.isnull().sum()*100/len(tel_df) # check for the missing value in dataframe
    for col in numv.columns:
        a = numv.loc[:,col].isnull().sum()/len(numv)*100
        if(a > 0):
            numv[col].fillna(numv.loc[:,col].median(), inplace = True)
        else:
            print("No missing value/NULL value existed")
    return numv

# Impute duplicate values (you can drop duplicate values) 
def removedup(tel_df):
    #Remove Duplicate
    dupes = tel_df.duplicated()
    z=sum(dupes)
    if (z>0):
        tel_df =tel_df.drop_duplicates()
    return tel_df

#Function importing Dataset
def importdata(path_to_csv1 , path_to_csv2):
    #Import CSV
    tel_df1 = pd.read_csv(path_to_csv1)
    tel_df2 = pd.read_csv(path_to_csv2)
    tel_df=tel_df1.merge(tel_df2, on = 'customerID')
    return tel_df

def levelEncoder(tf,tf_v):
    labelencoder = LabelEncoder()
    tf[tf_v] = labelencoder.fit_transform(tf[tf_v])
    return tf

#Encode the variables
def oneHotEncoder(iv):
    #One Hot Encode the data
    iv_en= pd.get_dummies(iv, columns=['gender','Partner','Dependents','PhoneService','MultipleLines','InternetService','OnlineSecurity','OnlineBackup','DeviceProtection','TechSupport','StreamingTV','StreamingMovies','Contract','PaperlessBilling','PaymentMethod'])
    return iv_en

# Drop the features using VIF factor
def vif_drop_feature(iv_en):
    #drop the dependent featires using VIF
    cols = iv_en.columns
    cols = cols.delete(0)
    X23 = iv_en[cols]
    for i in range(len(cols)):
        f_li = [vif(iv_en[cols].values, index) for index in range(len(cols))]
        m_vif = max(f_li)                     
        di = f_li.index(m_vif)
        if m_vif > 5:  
            cols = cols.delete(di)
    iv_en = iv_en[cols]
    return iv_en

#Drop Features 
def drop_feature_df(iv_en):
    #drop the uncessary features
    iv_en=iv_en.drop(['customerID','TotalCharges'],axis=1)
    return iv_en 

#Convert data types int to float
def int_to_float(iv_en):
    #Change the datatypes from int to float
    iv_en = iv_en.astype(float)
    return iv_en

# Function to preprocess the data
def preprocess_data(path_to_csv1 , path_to_csv2 , tf_v):
    tel_df = importdata(path_to_csv1 , path_to_csv2)
    iv , tf = seg_iv_dv(tel_df , tf_v)
    catv, numv = seg_cat_num(iv)
    numv = imputmissing(numv, tel_df)
    iv = merge_df(catv , numv)
    tel_def = removedup(tel_df)
    tf = levelEncoder(tf,tf_v)  
    iv_en = oneHotEncoder(iv)
    iv_en = drop_feature_df(iv_en)
    iv_en = int_to_float(iv_en)
    iv_en = vif_drop_feature(iv_en)
    tel_df = merge_df(iv_en , tf)
    tel_df = tel_df.astype(float)
    return tel_df, tf

def zScore(tel_df):
    scaled_tel_df = tel_df.apply(zscore)
    return scaled_tel_df
    
# Function to split the dataset
def splitdataset(tel_df , tf_v):
    # Separating the target variable
    X, y=seg_iv_dv(tel_df , tf_v)
    # Splitting the dataset into train and test
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size = 0.3, random_state = 100)  
    return X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test

#Build multiple models.
def train_modals(X_train, y_train):
  
    lr = LinearRegression()
    lr.fit(X_train, y_train)
    ridge = Ridge()
    ridge.fit(X_train, y_train)
    modell = LogisticRegression(solver="liblinear")
    modell.fit(X_train, y_train)
    modelg = GaussianNB()
    modelg.fit(X_train, y_train)
    knn = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors= 5 )
    knn.fit(X_train, y_train)
    clf = svm.SVC() 
    clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
    rfc = RandomForestClassifier()
    rfc.fit(X_train, y_train)
    return lr,ridge,modell,modelg,knn,clf,rfc

# Function to make predictions
def prediction(X_train, X_test, lr,ridge,modell,modelg,knn,clf,rfc):
    y_pred_lr_n = lr.predict(X_train)
    y_pred_lr_t = lr.predict(X_test)
    y_pred_ridge_n = ridge.predict(X_train)
    y_pred_ridge_t = ridge.predict(X_test)
    y_pred_modell_n = modell.predict(X_train)
    y_pred_modell_t = modell.predict(X_test)
    y_pred_modelg_n = modelg.predict(X_train)
    y_pred_modelg_t = modelg.predict(X_test)
    y_pred_knn_n = knn.predict(X_train)
    y_pred_knn_t = knn.predict(X_test)
    y_pred_clf_n = clf.predict(X_train)
    y_pred_clf_t = clf.predict(X_test)
    y_pred_rfc_n = rfc.predict(X_train)
    y_pred_rfc_t = rfc.predict(X_test)
    
    return y_pred_lr_n,y_pred_lr_t,y_pred_ridge_n,y_pred_ridge_t,y_pred_modell_n,y_pred_modell_t,y_pred_modelg_n,y_pred_modelg_t,y_pred_knn_n,y_pred_knn_t,y_pred_clf_n,y_pred_clf_t,y_pred_rfc_n,y_pred_rfc_t

# Function to calculate accuracy
def performance_matrics(y_train, y_test, y_pred_lr_n,y_pred_lr_t,y_pred_ridge_n,y_pred_ridge_t,y_pred_modell_n,y_pred_modell_t,y_pred_modelg_n,y_pred_modelg_t,y_pred_knn_n,y_pred_knn_t,y_pred_clf_n,y_pred_clf_t,y_pred_rfc_n,y_pred_rfc_t,lr,ridge,modell,modelg,knn,clf,rfc):
    
    #Linear Regression
    
    lr_train_r2=r2_score(y_train,y_pred_lr_n)*100
    lr_test_r2=r2_score(y_test,y_pred_lr_t)*100
    lr_train_mse=mean_squared_error(y_train,y_pred_lr_n)
    lr_test_mse=mean_squared_error(y_test,y_pred_lr_t)
    
    lr_results_df = pd.DataFrame([lr,lr_train_r2, lr_test_r2, lr_train_mse,lr_test_mse]).transpose()
    lr_results_df.columns = ['Method','Training R2/Train Accuracy','Test R2/Test Accuracy','Training MSE','Test MSE']
    
    #RIDGE 
    
    r_train_r2=r2_score(y_train,y_pred_ridge_n)*100
    r_test_r2=r2_score(y_test,y_pred_ridge_t)*100
    r_train_mse=mean_absolute_error(y_train,y_pred_ridge_n)
    r_test_mse=mean_squared_error(y_test,y_pred_ridge_t)
    r_results_df = pd.DataFrame([ridge, r_train_r2, r_test_r2, r_train_mse,r_test_mse]).transpose()
    r_results_df.columns = ['Method','Training R2/Train Accuracy','Test R2/Test Accuracy','Training MSE','Test MSE']
    
    #Logistic Regression
    
    l_train_acc=accuracy_score(y_train,y_pred_modell_n)*100
    l_test_acc=accuracy_score(y_test,y_pred_modell_t)*100
    l_train_pre=precision_score(y_train, y_pred_modell_n)
    l_test_pre=precision_score(y_test, y_pred_modell_t)
    l_train_re=recall_score(y_train, y_pred_modell_n)
    l_test_re=recall_score(y_test, y_pred_modell_t)
    l_train_f=f1_score(y_train, y_pred_modell_n)
    l_test_f=f1_score(y_test, y_pred_modell_t)
    l_results_df = pd.DataFrame([modell,l_train_acc,l_test_acc,l_train_pre, l_test_pre,l_train_re,l_test_re,l_train_f,l_test_f,]).transpose()
    l_results_df.columns = ['Method','Training R2/Train Accuracy','Test R2/Test Accuracy','Train Precision','Test Precision','Train Recall','Test Recall','Train F1-Score','Test F1-Score']
    
    #Gaussian 
    
    g_train_acc=accuracy_score(y_train,y_pred_modelg_n)*100
    g_test_acc=accuracy_score(y_test,y_pred_modelg_t)*100
    g_train_pre=precision_score(y_train, y_pred_modelg_n)
    g_test_pre=precision_score(y_test, y_pred_modelg_t)
    g_train_re=recall_score(y_train, y_pred_modelg_n)
    g_test_re=recall_score(y_test, y_pred_modelg_t)
    g_train_f=f1_score(y_train, y_pred_modelg_n)
    g_test_f=f1_score(y_test, y_pred_modelg_t)
    g_results_df = pd.DataFrame([modelg,g_train_acc,g_test_acc,g_train_pre, g_test_pre,g_train_re,g_test_re,g_train_f,g_test_f,]).transpose()
    g_results_df.columns = ['Method','Training R2/Train Accuracy','Test R2/Test Accuracy','Train Precision','Test Precision','Train Recall','Test Recall','Train F1-Score','Test F1-Score']
    
    #KNN
    
    k_train_acc=accuracy_score(y_train,y_pred_knn_n)*100
    k_test_acc=accuracy_score(y_test,y_pred_knn_t)*100
    k_train_pre=precision_score(y_train, y_pred_knn_n)
    k_test_pre=precision_score(y_test, y_pred_knn_t)
    k_train_re=recall_score(y_train, y_pred_knn_n)
    k_test_re=recall_score(y_test, y_pred_knn_t)
    k_train_f=f1_score(y_train, y_pred_knn_n)
    k_test_f=f1_score(y_test, y_pred_knn_t)
    k_results_df = pd.DataFrame([knn, k_train_acc,k_test_acc,k_train_pre, k_test_pre,k_train_re,k_test_re,k_train_f,k_test_f,]).transpose()
    k_results_df.columns = ['Method','Training R2/Train Accuracy','Test R2/Test Accuracy','Train Precision','Test Precision','Train Recall','Test Recall','Train F1-Score','Test F1-Score']
    
    #Support Vector Machine  
    
    s_train_acc=accuracy_score(y_train,y_pred_clf_n)*100
    s_test_acc=accuracy_score(y_test,y_pred_clf_t)*100
    s_train_pre=precision_score(y_train, y_pred_clf_n)
    s_test_pre=precision_score(y_test, y_pred_clf_t)
    s_train_re=recall_score(y_train, y_pred_clf_n)
    s_test_re=recall_score(y_test, y_pred_clf_t)
    s_train_f=f1_score(y_train, y_pred_clf_n)
    s_test_f=f1_score(y_test, y_pred_clf_t)
    s_results_df = pd.DataFrame([clf, s_train_acc,s_test_acc,s_train_pre, s_test_pre,s_train_re,s_test_re,s_train_f,s_test_f]).transpose()
    s_results_df.columns = ['Method','Training R2/Train Accuracy','Test R2/Test Accuracy','Train Precision','Test Precision','Train Recall','Test Recall','Train F1-Score','Test F1-Score']
    
    #Random Forest Classifier  
    
    r_train_acc=accuracy_score(y_train,y_pred_rfc_n)*100
    r_test_acc=accuracy_score(y_test,y_pred_rfc_t)*100
    r_train_pre=precision_score(y_train, y_pred_rfc_n)
    r_test_pre=precision_score(y_test, y_pred_rfc_t)
    r_train_re=recall_score(y_train, y_pred_rfc_n)
    r_test_re=recall_score(y_test, y_pred_rfc_t)
    r_train_f=f1_score(y_train, y_pred_rfc_n)
    r_test_f=f1_score(y_test, y_pred_rfc_t)
   
    
    rf_results_df = pd.DataFrame(['RandomForestClassifier()',r_train_acc,r_test_acc,r_train_pre, r_test_pre,r_train_re,r_test_re,r_train_f,r_test_f]).transpose()
    rf_results_df.columns = ['Method','Training R2/Train Accuracy','Test R2/Test Accuracy','Train Precision','Test Precision','Train Recall','Test Recall','Train F1-Score','Test F1-Score']
    
    df_results = pd.concat([lr_results_df,r_results_df,l_results_df,g_results_df,k_results_df,s_results_df,rf_results_df])
    
    return df_results
    

    
    
#Building Modal 
def building_modal(tel_df , tf_v):
    iv , tf = seg_iv_dv(tel_df , tf_v)
    scaled_iv = zScore(iv)
    scaled_tel_df = merge_df(scaled_iv , tf)
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = splitdataset(scaled_tel_df, tf_v)
    #Splitted the data in 30% to 70% successfully
    lr,ridge,modell,modelg,knn,clf,rfc = train_modals(X_train, y_train)
    #All models have trained successfully
    #performance_train_test_score(X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, lr,ridge,lasso,modell,modelg,knn,clf,rfc)
    y_pred_lr_n,y_pred_lr_t,y_pred_ridge_n,y_pred_ridge_t,y_pred_modell_n,y_pred_modell_t,y_pred_modelg_n,y_pred_modelg_t,y_pred_knn_n,y_pred_knn_t,y_pred_clf_n,y_pred_clf_t,y_pred_rfc_n,y_pred_rfc_t = prediction(X_train, X_test, lr,ridge,modell,modelg,knn,clf,rfc)
    #Pridiction successfully 
    df_results=performance_matrics(y_train,y_test, y_pred_lr_n,y_pred_lr_t,y_pred_ridge_n,y_pred_ridge_t,y_pred_modell_n,y_pred_modell_t,y_pred_modelg_n,y_pred_modelg_t,y_pred_knn_n,y_pred_knn_t,y_pred_clf_n,y_pred_clf_t,y_pred_rfc_n,y_pred_rfc_t,lr,ridge,modell,modelg,knn,clf,rfc)
    #Performance Matrics generated
    return df_results, X_test, y_test
